         <abstract>
            <p>Stable arrangements of electrons in equilibrium on the surface of a sphere have been obtained for most of the cases up to 14 electrons. They resemble the arrangements of the contact points of the faces of an n-hedron of least volume circumscribed about the sphere, except for n = 8. In this case, it is shown that the electrons near the contact points are in equilibrium, but the arrangement is not stable.</p>
         </abstract>
